Annotation Interface JS.Code

Enclosing class:
JS
@Retention(RUNTIME) @Target(TYPE) public static @interface JS.Code
A snippet of JavaScript code that must be included in the image. The specified JavaScript code is meant to contain JavaScript declarations that are necessary for the annotated Java class to work properly. The JavaScript code runs before any other code in the image. If the class annotated with this annotation is included in the image, then the specified JavaScript code is executed when the image code is loaded. If the analysis concludes that this class should not be included in the image, then specified JavaScript code may also not be included. This annotation can be applied to the same class more than once. See also JS.Code.Include for a way to include a JavaScript file instead of a JavaScript snippet.
